  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "We have defined two static cluster, one for ADS and another static cluster of type EDS with ADS as the EDS Config. Envoy crashes while initializing the Static Cluster.\r\n\r\nHere is the boot strap config\r\n\r\n```\r\nnode:\r\n  id: id_1\r\n  cluster: test_cluster\r\nadmin:\r\n  access_log_path: /tmp/admin_access.log\r\n  address:\r\n    socket_address: { address: 127.0.0.1, port_value: 9901 }\r\ndynamic_resources:\r\n  ads_config:\r\n    api_type: GRPC\r\n    cluster_names: [xds_cluster]\r\n  lds_config: {ads: {}}\r\n  cds_config: {ads: {}}\r\nstatic_resources:\r\n  clusters:\r\n  - name: xds_cluster\r\n    connect_timeout: 0.25s\r\n    type: STRICT_DNS\r\n    lb_policy: ROUND_ROBIN\r\n    http2_protocol_options: {} \r\n    hosts:\r\n      socket_address:\r\n        address: 127.0.0.1\r\n        port_value: 15001\r\n  - name: test\r\n    connect_timeout: 0.25s\r\n    type: EDS\r\n    eds_cluster_config:\r\n      eds_config: {ads: {}}\r\n    lb_policy: ROUND_ROBIN\r\n    http2_protocol_options: {} \r\n```\r\nEnvoy crashes while loading the \"test\" cluster.\r\n**Debug Notes:**\r\nIt is failing at `cluster_manager_impl` [constructor](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/master/source/common/upstream/cluster_manager_impl.cc#L211) \r\nThis is because, the cluster that is being initialized tries to use `ADS` but ADS is initialized after this call. \r\nWe need to ensure either ADS is initialized before or such clusters are initialized later.",
